n| Sangram \"Simmba\" Bhalerao\n|[[Rohit Shetty]]\n| Completed\n|-\n| 2020\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"background:#ffc;\"| ''[[Jayeshbhai Jordaar]]'' {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Jayeshbhai\n|[[Divyang Thakkar]]\n|Post-production<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-jayeshbhai-jordaar-ranveer-singh-and-shalini-pandey-head-to-gujarat-for-second-schedule-2808704|title='Jayeshbhai Jordaar': Ranveer Singh and Shalini Pandey head to Gujarat for second schedule|date=9 January 2020|accessdate=9 January 2020|work=Daily News and Analysis}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Discography==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders unsortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Album\n! scope=\"col\" |{{Tooltip|Ref(s).|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Asli Hip Hop\"\n| rowspan=\"7\"| 2019\n| rowspan=\"7\"| ''[[Gully Boy]]''\n| rowspan=\"7\";style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|title=Gully Boy (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack)|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/gully-boy-original-motion-picture-soundtrack/1450525267|publisher=iTunes|date=24 January 2019|accessdate=14 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190214174802/https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/gully-boy-original-motion-picture-soundtrack/1450525267|archive-date=14 February 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Mere Gully Mein\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Doori Poem\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Doori\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Kab Se Kab Tak\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Ek Hee Raasta\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Apna Time Aayega\"\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{{main|List of awards and nominations received by Ranveer Singh}}\nSingh is the recipient of four [[Filmfare Awards]]: [[Filmfare Award for Best Male Debut|Best Male Debut]] for ''Band Baaja Baaraat'' (2010), [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] for ''Bajirao Mastani'' (2016) and ''Gully Boy'' (2019), and [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actor|Best Actor (Critics)]] for ''Padmaavat'' (2018).\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n* {{IMDb name|3828984}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes person|ranveer_singh|Ranveer Singh}}\n* [http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebrity/ranveer-singh/ Ranveer Singh] at [[Bollywood Hungama]]\n\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Awards for Ranveer Singh\n| list =\n{{FilmfareAwardBestActor}}\n{{FilmfareCriticsAwardBestActor}}\n{{FilmfareAwardBestMaleDebut}}\n{{IIFAAwardBestActor}}\n{{IIFAAwardBestMaleDebut}}\n{{ProducersGuildFilmAwardBestActor}}\n{{ScreenAwardBestActor}}\n{{ScreenAwardBestMaleDebut}}\n{{ZeeCineAwardBestActorMale}}\n}}\n{{good article}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Singh, Ranveer}}\n[[Category:Ranveer Singh| ]]\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Indian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Indian male dancers]]\n[[Category:Indiana University alumni]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Hindi cinema]]\n[[Category:Sindhi people]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Mumbai]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:Filmfare Awards winners]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian actor}}\n{{Distinguish|Ranvir Singh}}\n{{pp-pc1}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=June 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Ranveer Singh\n| image              = Ranveer Singh promoting Bajirao Mastani.jpg\n| caption            = Singh promoting ''[[Bajirao Mastani]]'' in 2015\n| birth_name         = Ranveer Singh Bhavnani\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1985|7|6|df=y}}<ref name=\"ht2013-03-18\"/>\n| birth_place        = [[Bombay]], [[Maharashtra]], India\n| alma_mater         = [[Indiana University Bloomington|Indiana University]]\n| occupation         = Actor\n| yearsactive        = 2010\u2013present\n| spouse             = {{marriage|[[Deepika Padukone]]|2018}}\n| awards             = [[List of awards and nominations received by Ranveer Singh|Full list]]\n}}\n'''Ranveer Singh Bhavnani''' (born 6 July 1985) is an Indian actor who appears in [[Bollywood|Hindi films]]. The recipient of [[List of awards and nominations received by Ranveer Singh|several awards]], including four [[Filmfare Awards]], Singh is among the highest-paid actors in the country and has featured in ''[[Forbes India]]''{{'}}s [[Forbes Celebrity 100|Celebrity 100]] list since 2012.\n\nAfter completing a bachelor's degree from [[Indiana University Bloomington]], Singh returned to India to pursue a career in film. He briefly worked in advertising and made his acting debut in 2010 with a leading role in [[Yash Raj Films]]' romantic comedy ''[[Band Baaja Baaraat]]''. The film emerged as a critical and commercial success, earning him the [[Filmfare Award for Best Male Debut]]. He gained praise for playing a melancholic thief in the drama ''[[Lootera]]'' (2013), and established himself with his collaborations with [[Sanjay Leela Bhansali]], beginning with the romance ''[[Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela]]'' (2013).\n\nSingh gained critical acclaim for portraying [[Bajirao I]] and [[Alauddin Khalji|Alauddin Khilji]] in Bhansali's period dramas ''[[Bajirao Mastani]]'' (2015) and ''[[Padmaavat]]'' (2018), respectively. He won the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor]] for the former and the [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actor]] for the latter. These along with the action film ''[[Simmba]]'' (2018), in which he played the title character, rank among the [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest-grossing Indian films]]. He won another Filmfare Award for Best Actor for playing an aspiring rapper in [[Zoya Akhtar]]'s musical drama ''[[Gully Boy]]'' (2019). Singh is married to his frequent co-star [[Deepika Padukone]].\n\n==Early life and education==\nSingh was born on 6 July 1985<ref name=\"ht2013-03-18\"/> into a [[Sindhi people|Sindhi]] family in [[Mumbai|Bombay]] (now Mumbai), to Anju and Jagjit Singh Bhavnani.<ref>{{cite web|title=Filmfare Awards: Ranveer's sweet whispers for Deepika |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Filmfare-Awards-Ranveers-sweet-whispers-for-Deepika/articleshow/50619663.cms |publisher=[[Times of India]] |date=18 January 2016 |accessdate=24 May 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160123015119/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Filmfare-Awards-Ranveers-sweet-whispers-for-Deepika/articleshow/50619663.cms |archivedate=23 January 2016 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Quirky, cool, high on life: Why Ranveer Singh is the face of young India |first=Sameeksha |last=Dandriyal |url=http://www.ibnlive.com/news/movies/quirky-cool-high-on-life-why-ranveer-singh-is-the-face-of-young-india-1016613.html |publisher=[[International Business Times]] |date=6 July 2015 |accessdate=11 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150709022418/http://www.ibnlive.com/news/movies/quirky-cool-high-on-life-why-ranveer-singh-is-the-face-of-young-india-1016613.html |archivedate= 9 July 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n |title=Buddy bonding for Arjun Kapoor and Ranveer Singh \n |first=Upala \n |last=KBR \n |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/interview-buddy-bonding-for-arjun-kapoor-and-ranveer-singh-1959681 \n |publisher=[[Daily News and Analysis]] \n |date=6 February 2014 \n |accessdate=11 October 2015 \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151211145735/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/interview-buddy-bonding-for-arjun-kapoor-and-ranveer-singh-1959681 \n |archivedate=11 December 2015 \n |df= \n}}</ref> His grandparents moved to Bombay from [[Karachi]], [[Sindh]], in present-day [[Pakistan]], during the [[Partition of India]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/SUNDER-SINGH-BHAVNANI/articleshow/49848161.cms |title=SUNDER SINGH BHAVNANI - Times of India |accessdate=13 May 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161115145952/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/SUNDER-SINGH-BHAVNANI/articleshow/49848161.cms |archivedate=15 November 2016 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=I wish to visit Karachi once again: Ranveer Singh |first=Adnan |last=Lodhi |url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/1006855/i-wish-to-visit-karachi-once-again-ranveer-singh/ |publisher=[[The Express Tribune]] |date=9 December 2015 |accessdate=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160401234510/http://tribune.com.pk/story/1006855/i-wish-to-visit-karachi-once-again-ranveer-singh/ |archivedate= 1 April 2016 |df= }}</ref> He has an elder sister named Ritika Bhavnani.<ref name=\"ht2013-03-18\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Celebrity/Ranveer-Singh/1028316-Profile.aspx |title=Ranveer Singh: Celeb Bio|work=Hindustan Times |date=18 March 2013 |accessdate=19 December 2013|publisher=HT Media Ltd|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141224201603/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Celebrity/Ranveer-Singh/1028316-Profile.aspx|archivedate=24 December 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"throb\">{{cite news|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/ranveer-singh-the-new-heartthrob/761516/0|title=Ranveer Singh: The new heart-throb|last=Singh|first=Harneet|date=12 March 2011|accessdate=4 July 2011|work=[[The Indian Express]]|publisher=[[Indian Express Group]]}}</ref><ref name=\"bhbio\">{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/2835/%22I+was+born+with+the+gift+of+charming+women%22+-+Ranveer+Singh |title=Introducing: Ranveer Singh |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] |last=Ramsubramaniam |first=Nikhil |date=11 November 2010 |accessdate=20 November 2010 |pages=1\u20136 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023062718/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/2835/%22I%20was%20born%20with%20the%20gift%20of%20charming%20women%22%20-%20Ranveer%20Singh |archivedate=23 October 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mid-day.com/entertainment/2011/feb/230211-informer-8.htm |title=It's Ranveer Bhavnani and not Singh |work=[[Mid Day]] |publisher=MiD Day Infomedia Ltd |accessdate=11 March 2011 |date=23 February 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110226140743/http://www.mid-day.com/entertainment/2011/feb/230211-informer-8.htm |archivedate=26 February 2011 |df= }}</ref> Singh is the maternal third cousin of actress [[Sonam Kapoor]] daughter of actor [[Anil Kapoor]] and wife Sunita Kapoor (n\u00e9e Bhavnani).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mid-day.com/entertainment/2010/dec/141210-informer-5.htm |title=Band Baaja Baraat hero distant cousin of Sonam? |date=14 December 2010 |accessdate=14 December 2010 |work=Mid Day |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101217070234/http://www.mid-day.com/entertainment/2010/dec/141210-informer-5.htm |archivedate=17 December 2010 |df= }}</ref> Singh explains that he dropped his surname Bhavnani, since he felt that the name would have been \"too long, too many syllables\", thus downplaying his brand as a \"saleable commodity\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/did-you-know-/Why-did-Ranveer-Singh-drop-his-sur-name/articleshow/28277610.cms? |title=Why did Ranveer Singh drop his sur name? |last=Vyavahare |first=Renuka |date=2 January 2014 |accessdate=2 January 2014 |work=The Times of India |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141116095920/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/did-you-know-/Why-did-Ranveer-Singh-drop-his-sur-name/articleshow/28277610.cms |archivedate=16 November 2014 |df= }}</ref>\n\nSingh always aspired to be an actor, participating in several school plays and debates.<ref name=\"glam\">{{cite web|url=http://www.glamsham.com/movies/interviews/09-ranveer-singh-interview-121014.asp |title=Interview: Ranveer Singh |date=9 December 2010 |accessdate=29 January 2011 |publisher=Glamsham.com. Fifth Quarter Infomedia Pvt. Ltd |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101212220115/http://www.glamsham.com/movies/interviews/09-ranveer-singh-interview-121014.asp |archivedate=12 December 2010 |df= }}</ref> Once when he had gone for a birthday party, his grandmother asked him to dance and entertain her.<ref name=\"star\">{{cite journal|url=http://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/discussion/ranveer-singh-star-magazine-star-born-do-you-agree-or-not |title=Ranveer Singh&nbsp;\u2013 A Star Is Born |last=Varde |first=Ashwin |date=24 December 2010 |journal=Starweek Magazine |publisher=Magna Publication Co. Ltd |location=Mumbai, India |pages=23\u201327 |accessdate=31 December 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101229210546/http://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/discussion/ranveer-singh-star-magazine-star-born-do-you-agree-or-not |archivedate=29 December 2010 |df= }}</ref> Singh remembers that he suddenly jumped in the lawn and started dancing to the song \"Chumma Chumma\" from the 1991 action film, ''[[Hum (film)|Hum]]''.<ref name=\"glam\"/> He felt the thrill of performing and was interested in acting and dancing.<ref name=\"glam\"/> However, after he joined [[H.R. College of Commerce and Economics]] in Mumbai, Singh realised that getting a break in the film industry was not at all easy, as it was mostly people with a film background who got these opportunities. Feeling that the idea of acting was \"too far-fetched\", Singh focused on creative writing.<ref name=\"glam\"/> He went to the [[United States]] where he received his Bachelor of Arts degree from [[Indiana University Bloomington|Indiana University]].<ref name=\"bhbio\"/>\n\nAt the university, he decided to take acting classes and took up theatre as his [[minor (academic)|minor]].<ref name=\"glam\"/> After completing his studies and returning to Mumbai in 2007, Singh worked for a few years in advertising as a copywriter, with agencies like [[Ogilvy & Mather|O&M]] and [[J. Walter Thompson]].<ref name=\"bhbio\"/><ref name=\"star\"/> He then worked as an assistant director, but left it to pursue acting. He then decided to send his portfolio to directors.<ref name=\"star\"/>  He would go for all kinds of auditions, but did not get any good opportunities, while only getting calls for minor roles: \"Everything was so bleak. It was very frustrating. There were times I would think whether I was doing the right thing or not.\"<ref name=\"star\"/>\n\n==Career==\n\n===Film debut and breakthrough (2010\u20132014)===\n[[File:Ranveer2.jpg|left|thumb|Singh at a promotional event for ''[[Band Baaja Baaraat]]'' in 2010|alt=Singh looking towards his left and smiling, wearing a black T-shirt]]\nIn January 2010, Singh was called for an audition by Shanoo Sharma, the head of the casting division for [[Yash Raj Films]].<ref name=\"star\"/> They informed him that it was for a lead role in their film titled ''[[Band Baaja Baaraat]]'', a [[romantic comedy]] set in the world of [[wedding planner|wedding planning]]. [[Aditya Chopra]], the vice president of the company, later saw the audition tapes on video and was impressed by Singh's acting, and decided that he fit the part of Bittoo Sharma, the hero of the film.<ref name=\"ndtv\">{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/article177227.ece |title=YRF launches new face with Anushka Sharma |publisher=[[New Indian Express]] |date=4 February 2010 |accessdate=20 November 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131223030326/http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/article177227.ece |archivedate=23 December 2013 |df= }}</ref> However, the director [[Maneesh Sharma]] needed some more convincing and he was called for a few more auditions over the next two weeks until they were completely convinced of his caliber.<ref name=\"bhbio\"/> After the two weeks of testing, Singh was confirmed for the role of Bittoo, with [[Anushka Sharma]] playing the female lead.<ref name=\"ndtv\"/>\n\nSingh described the role of Bittoo Sharma as a typical Delhi boy.<ref name=\"bhbio\"/> To prepare for the role, he spent time with students at the [[University of Delhi|Delhi University]] campus.<ref name=\"glam\"/> Prior to the release of the film, trade analysts were skeptical of the film's commercial potential, citing the middling response to [[Yash Raj Films]]' last few productions, the lack of a male [[Movie star|star]] and the fact that the female lead, Anushka Sharma, was by then an \"almost-forgotten\" actress.<ref>{{cite web|first=Dipti |last=Nagpaul D'souza |url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/Missing-the-mark/707404/ |title=Missing the mark |work=[[The Indian Express]] |publisher=[[Indian Express Group]] |date=5 November 2010 |accessdate=31 January 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101209180544/http://www.indianexpress.com/news/Missing-the-mark/707404 |archivedate= 9 December 2010 |df= }}</ref> However, ''Band Baaja Baaraat'' went on to become a [[sleeper hit]]. Singh's portrayal of Bittoo was praised, with [[Anupama Chopra]] of [[NDTV]] writing that Singh was \"pitch perfect in the role of the uncouth but good-hearted small town slacker who is a bit of a duffer when it comes to matters of the heart.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/movie-review-band-baaja-baaraat-577 |title=Movie Review, Band Baaja Baaraat |date=10 December 2010 |accessdate=31 January 2011 |last=Chopra |first=Anupama |authorlink=Anupama Chopra |publisher=[[NDTV]] |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131109011228/http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/movie-review-band-baaja-baaraat-577 |archivedate= 9 November 2013 |df= }}</ref> The film earned approximately {{INRConvert|214|m}} at the domestic box office.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=2440&nCat=box_office_news|title=Band Baaja Baaraat 5th Week Scores Over Tees Maar Khan 3rd Week|date=17 January 2011|publisher=Box Office India|accessdate=31 January 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110120145744/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=2440&nCat=box_office_news|archivedate=20 January 2011 }}</ref> At the [[Filmfare Awards|56th Filmfare Awards]], Singh won the award for [[Filmfare Award for Best Male Debut|Best Male Debut]].<ref name=\"filmfare\">{{cite web|url=http://www.glamsham.com/movies/scoops/11/jan/31-56th-filmfare-awards-2010-a-night-of-glitz-n-glamour-011105.asp |title=56th Filmfare Awards 2010, A Night Of Glitz N' Glamour |date=29 January 2011 |accessdate=31 January 2011 |publisher=Glamsham.com. Fifth Quarter Infomedia Pvt. Ltd |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110203012043/http://www.glamsham.com/movies/scoops/11/jan/31-56th-filmfare-awards-2010-a-night-of-glitz-n-glamour-011105.asp |archivedate= 3 February 2011 |df= }}</ref>\n\nFollowing ''Band Baaja Baarat'', Singh signed on for ''[[Ladies vs Ricky Bahl]]'', a romantic comedy produced by Chopra and directed by Maneesh Sharma. He played a conman Ricky Bahl who cons girls for a living but finally meets his match. The film co-starred Anushka Sharma, [[Parineeti Chopra]], [[Dipannita Sharma]] and [[Aditi Sharma]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://businessofcinema.com/bollywood-news/yrfs-ladies-vs-ricky-bahl-goes-on-floors-in-delhi/33056 |title=YRF's Ladies V/S Ricky Bahl goes on floors in Delhi |date=6 April 2011 |accessdate=8 April 2011 |publisher=Business of Cinema |location=Mumbai |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023061344/http://businessofcinema.com/bollywood-news/yrfs-ladies-vs-ricky-bahl-goes-on-floors-in-delhi/33056 |archivedate=23 October 2013 |df= }}</ref> According to Singh, the title character had various avatars in the film, including a chirpy, entertaining side and a sinister side.<ref name=\"throb\"/> [[Nikhat Kazmi]] of ''[[The Times of India]]'' wrote, \"Ranveer is, well Ranveer: your average Joe kind of hero who looks convincing enough as Sunny, Deven, Iqbal, Ricky, his sundry avatars.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/hindi/Ladies-Vs-Ricky-Bahl/movie-review/11030547.cms |title=Ladies Vs Ricky Bahl movie review |last=Kazmi |first=Nikhat |date=9 December 2011 |accessdate=12 December 2011 |work=The Times of India |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111212005042/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/hindi/Ladies-Vs-Ricky-Bahl/movie-review/11030547.cms |archivedate=12 December 2011 |df= }}</ref> Commercially, ''Ladies vs Ricky Bahl'' earned {{INRConvert|370|m}} domestically.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.koimoi.com/box-office/box-office-check-aditya-chopra-the-producer/ |title=Box Office Check: Aditya Chopra The Producer |last=Basu |first=Mohar |date=21 May 2013 |accessdate=24 June 2013 |publisher=Koimoi.com |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130614133145/http://www.koimoi.com/box-office/box-office-check-aditya-chopra-the-producer/ |archivedate=14 June 2013 |df= }}</ref>\n\nSingh's next release was ''[[Lootera]]'' (2013), a period romance, written and directed by [[Vikramaditya Motwane]], and co-starring [[Sonakshi Sinha]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/sonakshi-comfortable-with-indian-look/1/160503.html |title=Sonakshi comfortable with Indian look |date=18 November 2011 |accessdate=20 November 2011 |work=[[India Today]] |publisher=India Today, Inc |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111120212648/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/sonakshi-comfortable-with-indian-look/1/160503.html |archivedate=20 November 2011 |df= }}</ref> An adaptation of [[O. Henry]]'s short story ''[[The Last Leaf]]'', ''Lootera'' was critically acclaimed.<ref name=\"ht2012-03-02\">{{cite news |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/Sonakshi-Ranveer-s-Lootera-inspired-by-O-Henry-s-short-story/Article1-819638.aspx |title=Sonakshi-Ranveer's Lootera inspired by O Henry's short story |last=Bakshi |first=Dibyajyoti |date=2 March 2012 |accessdate=22 August 2012 |work=Hindustan Times |publisher=HT Media Ltd |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120618091145/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/Sonakshi-Ranveer-s-Lootera-inspired-by-O-Henry-s-short-story/Article1-819638.aspx |archivedate=18 June 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"ht2013-07-05\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/Lootera-a-slow-pace-romantic-saga-worth-watching-say-critics/Article1-1087457.aspx |title=Lootera: a slow pace romantic saga worth watching, say critics |work=Hindustan Times |date=5 July 2013 |accessdate=30 December 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131112201259/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/bollywood/Lootera-a-slow-pace-romantic-saga-worth-watching-say-critics/Article1-1087457.aspx |archivedate=12 November 2013 |df= }}</ref> [[Rajeev Masand]] of [[CNN-IBN]] wrote that Singh \"brings a quiet sensitivity to Varun, and occasionally a smoldering intensity. Offering a finely internalized performance, he leaves a lasting impression.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Masand |first=Rajeev |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/lootera-review-drop-whatever-youre-doing-and-soak-in-this-love-saga/404400-47-84.html |title='Lootera' review: Drop whatever you're doing and soak in this love saga |date=15 July 2013 |accessdate=20 November 2014 |publisher=[[CNN-IBN]] |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131215050534/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/lootera-review-drop-whatever-youre-doing-and-soak-in-this-love-saga/404400-47-84.html |archivedate=15 December 2013 |df= }}</ref> However, ''Lootera'' performed poorly at the box office.<ref name=\"boxoffice\">{{cite web |url=http://boxofficeindia.com/Star_Cast/actor_detail/ranveer_singh |title=Ranveer Singh |publisher=Box Office India |accessdate=20 December 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141102095133/http://boxofficeindia.com/Star_Cast/actor_detail/ranveer_singh |archivedate=2 November 2014 |df= }}</ref>\n\n[[File:Ranveer Singh, Sanjay Leela Bhansali and Deepika Padukone at RAM LEELA's trailer launch.jpg|thumb|upright=1.2|Singh with [[Deepika Padukone]] and [[Sanjay Leela Bhansali]] at an event for ''[[Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela]]'' in 2013]]\n \nSingh next starred opposite [[Deepika Padukone]] in [[Sanjay Leela Bhansali]]'s adaptation of [[William Shakespeare]]'s ''[[Romeo and Juliet]]'', entitled ''[[Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela]]'', in which he played Ram, a [[Gujarati people|Gujarati boy]] based on the character of [[Romeo]].<ref>{{cite news|title=First look Ram Leela: Meet Romeo Ranveer and Juliet Deepika |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/first-poster-of-ram-leela-ranveer-singh-deepika-padukone/1/247370.html |work=India Today |accessdate=16 July 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwCOFmHR?url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/first-poster-of-ram-leela-ranveer-singh-deepika-padukone/1/247370.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> Bhansali was impressed by Singh's performance in ''Band Baaja Baaraat'' and decided to cast him for the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/bollywood/ranveer-singh-to-romance-kareena-in-ram-leela_112369.html |title=Ranveer Singh to romance Kareena in 'Ram Leela' |date=30 May 2012 |accessdate=24 August 2012 |publisher=Zee News |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131017184332/http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/bollywood/ranveer-singh-to-romance-kareena-in-ram-leela_112369.html |archivedate=17 October 2013 |df= }}</ref> ''Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela'' generated positive reviews from critics, as did Singh's performance.<ref name=\"ht2013-11-15\">{{cite news |last=Uniyal |first=Parmita |title=Movie review: Bhansali's Ram-leela is his best ever, say critics |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/movie-review-bhansali-s-ram-leela-is-his-best-ever-say-critics/article1-1151490.aspx |accessdate=15 November 2013 |newspaper=Hindustan Times |date=15 November 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131115083944/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/movie-review-bhansali-s-ram-leela-is-his-best-ever-say-critics/article1-1151490.aspx |archivedate=15 November 2013 |df= }}</ref> Writing for ''[[India Today]]'', Rohit Khilnani commented that \"Singh has everything going for him here. His Bollywood hero entry scene lying down on a bike in the song 'Tattad Tattad' is outstanding. He learnt a new language to better his performance for the character Ram and it paid off. In his fourth film he has the presence of a star.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Khilnani |first=Rohit |title=Movie Review: Ram Leela is a spectacular show! |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/movie-review-ram-leela/1/324858.html |accessdate=15 November 2013 |work=India Today |date=15 November 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131115081937/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/movie-review-ram-leela/1/324858.html |archivedate=15 November 2013 |df= }}</ref> The film emerged as Singh's biggest commercial success,<ref>{{cite web|title=Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela' earns Rs 93.58 crores in opening weekend |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/131120/entertainment-bollywood/article/goliyon-ki-raasleela-ram-leela-earns-rs-9358-crores-opening |date=16 November 2013 |work=Deccan Chronicle |accessdate=22 November 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131123060809/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/131120/entertainment-bollywood/article/goliyon-ki-raasleela-ram-leela-earns-rs-9358-crores-opening |archivedate=23 November 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koimoi.com/box-office/ramleela-grosses-100-crore-worldwide-at-the-box-office/ |title=Ramleela Grosses 100 Crore Worldwide At The Box Office |publisher=Koimoi.com |accessdate=18 December 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203020135/http://www.koimoi.com/box-office/ramleela-grosses-100-crore-worldwide-at-the-box-office/ |archivedate= 3 December 2013 |df= |date=20 November 2013 }}</ref> with worldwide revenues of {{INRConvert|2.02|b}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=6306&nCat= |title=Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram - Leela Set For 200 Crore Worldwide |publisher=Box Office India |date=9 December 2013 |accessdate=18 December 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131215160117/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=6306&nCat=|archivedate=15 December 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koimoi.com/box-office/ramleela-all-set-to-join-koimois-top-worldwide-grossing-movies-list/ |title=Ramleela All Set To Join Koimoi's 'Top Worldwide Grossing Movies' List |publisher=Koimoi.com |date=11 December 2013 |accessdate=18 December 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131218105403/http://www.koimoi.com/box-office/ramleela-all-set-to-join-koimois-top-worldwide-grossing-movies-list/ |archivedate=18 December 2013 |df= }}</ref> For his portrayal, he received several recognitions, including a [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] nomination at Filmfare.<ref name=\"59filmfare\">{{cite news|title=59th Idea Filmfare Awards Nominations |url=http://www.filmfare.com/news/59th-idea-filmfare-awards-nominations-5138.html |accessdate=14 January 2014 |work=Filmfare |date=13 January 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140115044052/http://www.filmfare.com/news/59th-idea-filmfare-awards-nominations-5138.html |archivedate=15 January 2014 |df= }}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Singh starred as a Bengali criminal in [[Ali Abbas Zafar]]'s ''[[Gunday]]'', alongside [[Arjun Kapoor]], [[Priyanka Chopra]] and [[Irrfan Khan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-08-24/news-interviews/33365530_1_arjun-kapoor-ali-zafar-ranveer-singh|title=Ali Abbas and Yash Raj team up again|last=Misra|first=Iti Shree|date=24 August 2012|accessdate=2 January 2014|work=The Times of India|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131215024623/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-08-24/news-interviews/33365530_1_arjun-kapoor-ali-zafar-ranveer-singh|archive-date=15 December 2013|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}\n</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yashrajfilms.com/movies/MovieIndividual.aspx?MovieID=b1bae9c1-ca58-477e-b9fb-81d1e0fce6cc |title=Gunday |accessdate=2 January 2014 |publisher=Yash Raj Films |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131222091910/http://www.yashrajfilms.com/Movies/MovieIndividual.aspx?MovieID=b1bae9c1-ca58-477e-b9fb-81d1e0fce6cc |archivedate=22 December 2013 |df= }}</ref> David Chute of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' praised Singh's screen presence and wrote that he \"tucks the movie's center of interest under his arm and takes it with him \u2014 even though he has the could-be-thankless \"good brother\" role\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Chute |first=David |url=https://variety.com/2014/film/reviews/film-review-gunday-1201103256/ |title=Gunday Review- An Entertaining Buddy-Gangster Melodrama |work=Variety |accessdate=30 December 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141224124044/http://variety.com/2014/film/reviews/film-review-gunday-1201103256/ |archivedate=24 December 2014 |df= }}</ref> Also, Singh's chemistry with Kapoor was considered by critic Rohit Khilnani to the prime asset of the film.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/gunday-review-starring-priyanka-chopra-ranveer-singh-arjun-kapoor/1/343438.html |title=Movie review: Gunday is old wine in a new bottle, it tastes awesome! |author=Khilnani, Rohit |work=India Today |date=14 February 2014 |accessdate=25 February 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140224223702/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/gunday-review-starring-priyanka-chopra-ranveer-singh-arjun-kapoor/1/343438.html |archivedate=24 February 2014 |df= }}</ref> ''Gunday'' proved to be Singh's biggest box office opener,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/Details/art_detail/gundayfirstdaycollectionsreport |title=Boxoffice: Gunday First Day Collections |publisher=Box Office India |accessdate=15 February 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223120701/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/Details/art_detail/gundayfirstdaycollectionsreport |archivedate=23 February 2014 |df= }}</ref> and eventually emerged a box-office success with a revenue of {{INRConvert|1|b|}} worldwide.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/articles/540092/20140223/gunday-box-office-collection-100-crore-ranveer.htm |title='Gunday' Box Office Collection: Ranveer-Arjun Starrer Grosses 100 Crore Worldwide |author=Seshagiri, Sangeetha |work=International Business Times |date=23 February 2014 |accessdate=25 February 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223153527/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/articles/540092/20140223/gunday-box-office-collection-100-crore-ranveer.htm |archivedate=23 February 2014 |df= }}</ref> After a cameo appearance in ''[[Finding Fanny]]'', Singh starred as a gangster in [[Shaad Ali]]'s unsuccessful crime drama ''[[Kill Dil]]'' opposite Parineeti Chopra and [[Ali Zafar]] and received negative reviews.<ref>{{cite news|title=After Ramleela, Ranveer Singh and Deepika Padukone to share screen space in Finding Fanny Fernandes |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/1901468/report-after-ramleela-ranveer-singh-and-deepika-padukone-to-share-screen-space-in-finding-fanny-fernandes |accessdate=20 October 2013 |newspaper=Daily News and Analysis |date=10 October 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014000603/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/1901468/report-after-ramleela-ranveer-singh-and-deepika-padukone-to-share-screen-space-in-finding-fanny-fernandes |archivedate=14 October 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title='Kill Dil' gets 'kill'ed officially; collects a mere Rs 20 crore in opening weekend |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/kill-dil-gets-killed-officially-collects-a-mere-rs-13-crore-in-opening-weekend/#sthash.OigToazn.dpuf |accessdate=20 December 2014 |newspaper=The Indian Express |date=17 November 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141220142823/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/kill-dil-gets-killed-officially-collects-a-mere-rs-13-crore-in-opening-weekend/ |archivedate=20 December 2014 |df= }}</ref>\n\n===Established actor (2015\u2013present)===\n[[File:Ranveer at filmfare (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|left|Singh at the [[61st Filmfare Awards]] ceremony, where he won the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] award for portraying [[Bajirao I]] in ''[[Bajirao Mastani]]'' (2015)]]\nIn [[Zoya Akhtar]]'s ensemble comedy-drama ''[[Dil Dhadakne Do]]'' (2015), Singh starred with [[Anil Kapoor]], [[Shefali Shah]] and Priyanka Chopra as the younger sibling of a dysfunctional Punjabi business family who aspires to become a pilot. Writing for ''[[Mumbai Mirror]]'', Kunal Guha found Singh to be the \"surprise element\" of the film; he praised his \"immaculate comic timing\" and took note of his subtlety.<ref>{{cite news|last=Guha |first=Kunal |title=Film Review: Dil Dhadakne Do |url=http://www.mumbaimirror.com/entertainment/bollywood/Film-review-Dil-Dhadakne-Do/articleshow/47547376.cms |work=[[Mumbai Mirror]] |date=5 June 2015 |accessdate=5 June 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150606131650/http://www.mumbaimirror.com/entertainment/bollywood/Film-review-Dil-Dhadakne-Do/articleshow/47547376.cms |archivedate= 6 June 2015 |df= }}</ref> Commercially, the film underperformed.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficeindia.com/movie.php?movieid=2879 |title=Dil Dhadakne Do |publisher=Box Office India |accessdate=14 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190214233318/https://boxofficeindia.com/movie.php?movieid=2879 |archive-date=14 February 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Singh next reunited with Sanjay Leela Bhansali in the period romance ''[[Bajirao Mastani]]'' (2015), opposite Deepika Padukone and Priyanka Chopra. He portrayed [[Bajirao I]], for which he shaved his head and to prepare, he locked himself in a hotel room for 21 days.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Exclusive-Ranveer-Singh-shaves-his-head-for-Bajirao-Mastani/articleshow/44887453.cms |title=Exclusive: Ranveer Singh shaves his head for Bajirao Mastani |last=Gupta |first=Priya |work=The Times of India |date=21 October 2014 |accessdate=19 December 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150216022938/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Exclusive-Ranveer-Singh-shaves-his-head-for-Bajirao-Mastani/articleshow/44887453.cms |archivedate=16 February 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=When Ranveer Singh locked himself up in a hotel room for 21 days |url=http://www.mid-day.com/articles/when-ranveer-singh-locked-himself-up-in-a-hotel-room-for-21-days/16770197 |work=Mid Day |date=14 December 2015 |accessdate=19 December 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151216203114/http://www.mid-day.com/articles/when-ranveer-singh-locked-himself-up-in-a-hotel-room-for-21-days/16770197 |archivedate=16 December 2015 |df= }}</ref> [[Raja Sen]] wrote that Singh \"brings his character to life and does so with both machismo and grace\", and commended him for his perfecting his character's gait and accent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-priyanka-ranveer-are-terrific-in-bajirao-mastani/20151218.htm |title=Review: Priyanka, Ranveer are terrific in Bajirao Mastani |last=Sen |first=Raja |publisher=Rediff.com |date=18 December 2015 |accessdate=19 December 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151220070433/http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-priyanka-ranveer-are-terrific-in-bajirao-mastani/20151218.htm |archivedate=20 December 2015 |df= }}</ref> The film earned {{INRConvert|3.5|b}} to become one of the [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest-grossing Indian films]], and garnered Singh the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/art_detail.php?articalid=1734 |title=Worldwide 2015 \u2013 Dilwale Nearing Prem Ratan Dhan Payo |date=14 January 2016 |publisher=Box Office India |accessdate=24 January 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160117060809/http://boxofficeindia.com/art_detail.php?articalid=1734 |archivedate=17 January 2016 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"win\">{{cite news|url=http://www.filmfare.com/news/full-list-of-winners-of-the-61st-britannia-filmfare-awards-11841.html |title=Full list of winners of the 61st Britannia Filmfare Awards |work=Filmfare |date=15 January 2016 |accessdate=16 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160316165017/http://www.filmfare.com/news/full-list-of-winners-of-the-61st-britannia-filmfare-awards-11841.html |archivedate=16 March 2016 |df= }}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Singh starred in Aditya Chopra's comedy-romance ''[[Befikre]]'' opposite [[Vaani Kapoor]]. He played Dharam Gulati, a stand-up comic whose romantic liaisons with Kapoor's character leads to conflict between them. Set in Paris, ''Befikre'' marked the fourth project to be directed by Chopra.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/befikre-review-round-heres-what-critics-have-say-about-ranveer-singh-vaani-kapoors-parisian-707617 |title=Befikre review round-up: Critics have given their verdict on Ranveer Singh and Vaani Kapoor's film |last=Sarkar |first=Prarthna |publisher=International Business Times |date=9 December 2016 |accessdate=10 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161210131156/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/befikre-review-round-heres-what-critics-have-say-about-ranveer-singh-vaani-kapoors-parisian-707617 |archivedate=10 December 2016 |df= }}</ref> Singh performed a nude scene for it, a rare occurrence in an Indian film.<ref>{{cite news|last=Mehta|first=Sushant|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/gossip/story/ranveer-singh-butt-naked-vaani-kapoor-befikre-interview-346592-2016-10-14|title=Exclusive: Ranveer Singh has gone butt naked for Befikre. For real!|work=India Today|date=14 October 2016|access-date=24 January 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180125022316/https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/gossip/story/ranveer-singh-butt-naked-vaani-kapoor-befikre-interview-346592-2016-10-14|archivedate=25 January 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Jay Weissberg of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' found the film to be an \"overly energetic twist on the old friends with benefits theme\" and criticised Singh's \"manic behavior\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Weissberg|first=Jay|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/reviews/befikre-film-review-1201950595/|title=Film Review: 'Befikre'|date=3 January 2017|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|access-date=3 January 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170104050548/http://variety.com/2017/film/reviews/befikre-film-review-1201950595/|archivedate=4 January 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref> It underperformed at the box office.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://boxofficeindia.com/movie.php?movieid=3437|title=Befikre|publisher=Box Office India|access-date=24 January 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171008200322/https://boxofficeindia.com/movie.php?movieid=3437|archivedate=8 October 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nAfter a year-long absence from the screen, Singh portrayed [[Alauddin Khalji|Alauddin Khilji]], a ruthless Muslim king, in Sanjay Leela Bhansali's period drama ''[[Padmaavat]]'' (2018), co-starring Deepika Padukone and [[Shahid Kapoor]], which marked his third collaboration with Bhansali and Padukone.<ref name=\"padmavati\">{{cite news|title=Team Padmavati starts shooting today |url=http://www.filmfare.com/news/team-padmavati-starts-shooting-today-16399.html |accessdate=1 November 2016 |work=Filmfare |date=1 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161101164843/http://www.filmfare.com/news/team-padmavati-starts-shooting-today-16399.html |archivedate= 1 November 2016 |df= }}</ref> [[Saffron terror|Right-wing Hindu groups]]&nbsp;speculated that the film distorted historical facts, and issued violent threats against the cast and crew. The film's release was deferred and was allowed for exhibition after several modifications were made to it.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ray |first=Saptarshi |title=Bounty placed on Bollywood actress' head after Hindu-Muslim film outrage |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/11/17/bounty-placed-bollywood-actress-head-hindu-muslim-film-outrage/ |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |date=17 November 2017 |accessdate=2 December 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171118052745/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/11/17/bounty-placed-bollywood-actress-head-hindu-muslim-film-outrage/ |archivedate=18 November 2017 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/film-padmavati-to-get-ua-certificate-title-may-be-changed-to-padmavat-1793855|title=Censor Board Wants \"Padmavati\" Renamed \"Padmavat\", 5 Changes To Film|publisher=NDTV|date=30 December 2017|accessdate=30 December 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171230133652/https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/film-padmavati-to-get-ua-certificate-title-may-be-changed-to-padmavat-1793855|archivedate=30 December 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Ankur Pathak of ''[[HuffPost]]'' criticised the film's misogynistic and regressive themes, but praised Singh for his \"astute brilliance\" in depicting Khilji's bisexuality.<ref>{{cite news|last=Pathak|first=Ankur|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.in/2018/01/23/padmaavat-review-ranveer-singhs-queer-act-shatters-the-glass-ceiling-in-indian-film-writing_a_23341645/|title='Padmaavat' Review: Ranveer Singh's Queer Act Shatters The Glass Ceiling In Indian Film Writing|date=24 January 2018|work=[[HuffPost]]|access-date=24 January 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180124061209/http://www.huffingtonpost.in/2018/01/23/padmaavat-review-ranveer-singhs-queer-act-shatters-the-glass-ceiling-in-indian-film-writing_a_23341645/|archivedate=24 January 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Rajeev Masand opined that he \"plays the part with the sort of grotesque flamboyance that makes it hard to look at anyone or anything else when he\u2019s on the screen\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Masand|first=Rajeev|url=http://www.news18.com/news/movies/padmaavat-movie-review-ranveer-singh-delicious-performance-is-its-biggest-strength-1639675.html|title=Padmaavat Movie Review: Ranveer Singh's Delicious Performance Is Its Biggest Strength|date=24 January 2018|publisher=News18|access-date=24 January 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180125020734/http://www.news18.com/news/movies/padmaavat-movie-review-ranveer-singh-delicious-performance-is-its-biggest-strength-1639675.html|archivedate=25 January 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref> ''Padmaavat''{{'}}s production budget of {{INRConvert|2|b}} made it the [[List of most expensive Indian films#Hindi|most expensive Hindi film]] ever made at that time.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=3469|title=Padmavati Being Aimed For A February Release|publisher=Box Office India|date=8 December 2017|accessdate=8 December 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171208231459/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=3469|archivedate=8 December 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref> With a worldwide gross of over {{INRConvert|5.7|b}}, it ranks as Singh's highest-grossing release and is among India cinema's biggest grossers.<ref name=\"2018w\"/><ref>\n{{cite web|url=https://boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=3881|title=Worldwide Alltime : Padmaavat 7th - Baaghi 2 22nd|accessdate=26 April 2018|date=26 April 2018|publisher=Box Office India|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180426213042/https://boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=3881|archive-date=26 April 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He won the [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actor]] (shared with [[Ayushmann Khurrana]] for ''[[Andhadhun]]'') and gained a Best Actor nomination at the ceremony.<ref>{{cite news|title=Winners of the 64th Vimal Filmfare Awards 2019|url=https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/all-winners-of-the-64th-vimal-filmfare-awards-2019_-33004-3.html|date=23 March 2019|accessdate=23 March 2019|work=[[Filmfare]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190323165124/https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/all-winners-of-the-64th-vimal-filmfare-awards-2019_-33004-3.html|archive-date=23 March 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/nominations-for-the-64th-vimal-filmfare-awards-2019_-32898-1.html |title=Nominations for the 64th Vimal Filmfare Awards 2019 |work=Filmfare |date=12 March 2019 |access-date=13 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190316052927/https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/nominations-for-the-64th-vimal-filmfare-awards-2019_-32898-1.html |archive-date=16 March 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n[[File:Ranveer Singh and Sara Ali Khan promote \u2018Simmba\u2019 at 98.3 FM Radio Mirchi.jpg|thumb|Singh and [[Sara Ali Khan]] promoting ''[[Simmba]]'' in 2018]]\n\nIn the same year, Singh played the titular corrupt policeman in [[Rohit Shetty]]'s action comedy ''[[Simmba]]'', based on the Telugu-language film ''[[Temper (film)|Temper]]'' (2015), co-starring [[Sara Ali Khan]] and [[Sonu Sood]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/ranveer-singh-stars-in-and-as-simmba-in-rohit-shetty-karan-johar-film-twitters-thrilled-1784625|title=Ranveer Singh Stars In And As Simmba In Rohit Shetty, Karan Johar Film. Twitter's Thrilled|work=NDTV|access-date=7 December 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171208003422/https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/ranveer-singh-stars-in-and-as-simmba-in-rohit-shetty-karan-johar-film-twitters-thrilled-1784625|archivedate=8 December 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/breaking-ranveer-singh-simmba-directed-rohit-shetty/|title = BREAKING: Ranveer Singh in and as Simmba; directed by Rohit Shetty|date = 7 December 2017|work = Bollywood Hungama|access-date = 12 December 2017|via = |url-status=live|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20171212193142/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/breaking-ranveer-singh-simmba-directed-rohit-shetty/|archivedate = 12 December 2017|df = dmy-all}}</ref> Despite disliking the film, Uday Bhatia of ''[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]]'' credited Singh for playing his \"cardboard creation\" of a character with an \"underlying sweetness that renders it more winsome than the humourless masculinity of [[Ajay Devgn|Devgn]]'s ''[[Singam (film series)|Singham]]''\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Bhatia|first=Uday|url=https://www.livemint.com/Consumer/ICrn1m7VU6y6Zv7kezOgJL/Simmba-movie-review-Crash-and-Burn.html|title='Simmba' movie review: Crash and Burn|date=28 December 2018|work=Mint|access-date=28 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181228091258/https://www.livemint.com/Consumer/ICrn1m7VU6y6Zv7kezOgJL/Simmba-movie-review-Crash-and-Burn.html|archive-date=28 December 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> With worldwide earnings of {{INRConvert|4|b}}, ''Simmba'' emerged as Singh's second [[List of Bollywood films of 2018|top-earning Indian film of 2018]].<ref name=\"2018w\">\n{{cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/box-office-collections/worldwide/2018/|title=Bollywood Top Grossers Worldwide: 2018|website=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=1 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190301141625/https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/box-office-collections/worldwide/2018/|archive-date=1 March 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}\n</ref>\n\nSingh next reteamed with Zoya Akhtar in ''[[Gully Boy]]'' (2019), a musical inspired by the life of the street rappers [[Divine (rapper)|Divine]] and [[Naezy (rapper)|Naezy]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/real-gully-boys-divine-and-naezy-praise-ranveer-singh-he-soaked-in-our-body-language-our-attitude/story-CXjwVVTUdyrE5CG3T85CXN.html|title=Real Gully Boys Divine and Naezy praise Ranveer Singh: He soaked in our body language, our attitude|work=Hindustan Times|date=6 February 2019|access-date=14 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190214174335/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/real-gully-boys-divine-and-naezy-praise-ranveer-singh-he-soaked-in-our-body-language-our-attitude/story-CXjwVVTUdyrE5CG3T85CXN.html|archive-date=14 February 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Singh found little in common with his character of a poor man who aspires to become a rapper, and in preparation he underwent acting workshops and spent time with both Divine and Naezy. He performed his own rap songs and was pleased that the film brought attention to India's underground music scene.<ref>{{cite news|author=Sharma, Priyanka|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/my-dna-is-simmba-not-gully-boy-ranveer-singh-5577673/|title=My DNA is Simmba, not Gully Boy: Ranveer Singh|work=The Indian Express|date=11 February 2019|access-date=14 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190214115625/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/my-dna-is-simmba-not-gully-boy-ranveer-singh-5577673/|archive-date=14 February 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The film premiered at the [[69th Berlin International Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite news|author=Ramachandran, Naman|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/spotlight/indian-hip-hop-gets-big-screen-time-in-berlin-festival-pic-gully-boy-1203138253/|title=Indian Hip-Hop Gets Big Screen Time in Berlin Festival Pic 'Gully Boy'|work=Variety|date=13 February 2019|access-date=14 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190213170049/https://variety.com/2019/film/spotlight/indian-hip-hop-gets-big-screen-time-in-berlin-festival-pic-gully-boy-1203138253/|archive-date=13 February 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Deborah Young of ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' commended him for displaying a \"pleasingly full emotional range that extends to drama and hip-hop\" and writing for [[Film Companion]], [[Baradwaj Rangan]] praised his ghetto accent and found his understated performance to be a \"superb showreel for his range\".<ref>{{cite news|author=Young, Deborah|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/gully-boy-review-1184114|title='Gully Boy' ('Apna Time Aayega'): Film Review; Berlin 2019|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=9 February 2019|access-date=14 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190214174809/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/gully-boy-review-1184114|archive-date=14 February 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Rangan, Baradwaj|url=https://www.filmcompanion.in/gully-boy-movie-review-berlin-film-festival-2019-ranveer-singh-zoya-akhtar-baradwaj-rangan|title=Gully Boy Movie Review: A Softer Than Expected, But Hugely Entertaining And Beautifully Made Street-Rapper Story|website=Film Companion|date=9 February 2019|access-date=14 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190216064028/https://www.filmcompanion.in/gully-boy-movie-review-berlin-film-festival-2019-ranveer-singh-zoya-akhtar-baradwaj-rangan|archive-date=16 February 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> ''Gully Boy'' won a record 13 Filmfare Awards, and Singh received another Best Actor award.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/filmfare-awards-2020-full-list-of-winners-gully-boy-s-13-wins-make-history-alia-bhatt-and-ranveer-singh-take-top-awards/story-JRWvCT8f2A8KxDy94AZYSI.html|title=Filmfare Awards 2020 full list of winners: Gully Boy\u2019s 13 wins make history, Alia Bhatt and Ranveer Singh take top awards|work=Hindustan Times|date=16 February 2020|accessdate=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n \nSingh will next reprise his role as Simmba in Shetty's action film ''[[Sooryavanshi]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://scroll.in/reel/954851/sooryavanshi-trailer-meet-the-khaki-posse-from-rohit-shettys-copverse|title=\u2018Sooryavanshi\u2019 trailer: Meet the khaki posse from Rohit Shetty\u2019s copverse|website=Scroll.in|date=2 March 2020|accessdate=2 March 2020}}</ref> He will portray the cricketer [[Kapil Dev]] in ''[[83 (film)|83]]'', a sports film based on the [[1983 Cricket World Cup]], and the [[Mughal Empire|Mughal]] prince [[Dara Shukoh|Dara Shikoh]] in [[Karan Johar]]'s historical drama ''Takht'', which features an ensemble cast including [[Kareena Kapoor]], Alia Bhatt, [[Bhumi Pednekar]], and [[Vicky Kaushal]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/ranveer-singh-is-super-excited-to-play-kapil-dev-in-kabir-khans-next-25300.html|title=Ranveer Singh is super excited to play Kapil Dev in Kabir Khan's next|work=Filmfare|access-date=11 December 2017|language=en|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171212031517/https://m.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/ranveer-singh-is-super-excited-to-play-kapil-dev-in-kabir-khans-next-25300.html|archivedate=12 December 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url = https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/takht-karan-johar-alia-bhatt-ranveer-singh-janhvi-kapoor-5298675/ |title = Takht: Karan Johar ropes in Alia Bhatt, Ranveer Singh, Janhvi Kapoor, Kareena Kapoor and others for his next directorial |date = 9 August 2018 |work = The Indian Express |access-date = 9 August 2018 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180809163439/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/takht-karan-johar-alia-bhatt-ranveer-singh-janhvi-kapoor-5298675/ |archive-date = 9 August 2018 |url-status=live |df = dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/ranveer-singh-to-play-dara-shikoh-while-vicky-kaushal-will-be-seen-as-aurangzeb-in-takht/articleshow/67234455.cms|title=Ranveer Singh to play Dara Shikoh while Vicky Kaushal will be seen as Aurangzeb in 'Takht'|work=The Times of India|date=24 December 2018|access-date=25 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181225091547/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/ranveer-singh-to-play-dara-shikoh-while-vicky-kaushal-will-be-seen-as-aurangzeb-in-takht/articleshow/67234455.cms|archive-date=25 December 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He has also committed to team with Yash Raj Films once again for the comedy ''[[Jayeshbhai Jordaar]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/ranveer-singh-on-bagging-jayeshbhai-jordaar-it-s-the-most-solid-on-paper-material-i-ve-come-across-1535425-2019-05-27|title=Ranveer Singh on bagging Jayeshbhai Jordaar: It's the most solid on-paper material I've come across|work=India Today|access-date=27 May 2019|date=27 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life and media image ==\n[[File:Deepika Padukone and Ranveer Singh reception.jpg|thumb|upright=1.2|Singh and Padukone at their wedding reception in 2018]]\nSingh began dating Deepika Padukone, his co-star in ''Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela'', in August 2012.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ranveer Singh: I haven't met anyone like Deepika Padukone, ever!|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/ranveer-singh-i-havent-met-anyone-like-deepika-padukone-ever/articleshow/67242687.cms|work=The Times of India|date=25 December 2018|accessdate=25 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181226115953/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/ranveer-singh-i-havent-met-anyone-like-deepika-padukone-ever/articleshow/67242687.cms|archive-date=26 December 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In October 2018, the couple announced their impending marriage.<ref>{{cite news|title=Deepika Padukone and Ranveer Singh announce wedding date|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/deepika-padukone-ranveer-singh-wedding-card-date-5411450/|work=The Indian Express|date=21 October 2018|accessdate=21 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181021190905/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/deepika-padukone-ranveer-singh-wedding-card-date-5411450/|archive-date=21 October 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The following month, they married in traditional [[Konkani]] [[Hindu]] and Sikh [[Anand Karaj]] (Singh's paternal grandfather is Sikh<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mid-day.com/photos/lesser-known-facts-about-ranveer-singh-before-he-became-a-star/17117|title=Lesser known facts about Ranveer Singh, before he became a star|website=mid-day|access-date=14 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190109162430/https://www.mid-day.com/photos/lesser-known-facts-about-ranveer-singh-before-he-became-a-star/17117|archive-date=9 January 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>) ceremonies at [[Lake Como]], Italy.<ref>{{cite news|title=Deepika Padukone, Ranveer Singh are married now, wedding ceremony ends in Italy|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/deepika-padukone-ranveer-singh-are-married-now-wedding-ceremony-ends-in-italy/story-OrrIJnMvTwI1wSwl7JbWqM.html|work=Hindustan Times|date=14 November 2018|accessdate=14 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181114143025/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/deepika-padukone-ranveer-singh-are-married-now-wedding-ceremony-ends-in-italy/story-OrrIJnMvTwI1wSwl7JbWqM.html|archive-date=14 November 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/ranveer-singh-deepika-padukone-wedding-sikh-body-upset-over-anand-karaj-performed-outside-gurdwara/story-gtw6h2BVs7F2tCD3VjK85K.html|title=Ranveer Singh-Deepika Padukone wedding: Sikh body upset over Anand Karaj performed outside gurdwara|date=19 November 2018|accessdate=19 December 2018|work=Hindustan Times|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181219134548/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/ranveer-singh-deepika-padukone-wedding-sikh-body-upset-over-anand-karaj-performed-outside-gurdwara/story-gtw6h2BVs7F2tCD3VjK85K.html|archive-date=19 December 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nSingh has appeared in ''[[Forbes India]]''{{'s}} [[Forbes Celebrity 100|Celebrity 100]] list since 2012, peaking at the seventh position in 2019.<ref name=\"Ranveer Singh\">{{cite news|title=Ranveer Singh|url=http://www.forbesindia.com/celebprofile2016/ranveer-singh/1587/23|work=[[Forbes]]|accessdate=22 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180822113743/http://www.forbesindia.com/celebprofile2016/ranveer-singh/1587/23|archive-date=22 August 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Ranveer Singh\"/><ref>{{cite news|title=2017 Celebrity 100|url=http://www.forbesindia.com/lists/2017-celebrity-100/1665/all|work=Forbes|accessdate=22 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180711185628/http://www.forbesindia.com/lists/2017-celebrity-100/1665/all|archive-date=11 July 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.forbesindia.com/lists/2019-celebrity-100/1819/all |title=2019 Celebrity 100 |work=Forbes India |accessdate=20 December 2018 }}</ref> That year, the magazine estimated his annual earnings to be {{INRConvert|1.18|b}} and ranked him as the fifth highest-paid actor in the country.<ref>{{cite news |last=Shah|first=Ruchika|url=http://www.forbesindia.com/article/2019-celebrity-100/2019-celebrity-100-what-the-money-says/56695/1 |title=2019 Celebrity 100: What the money says |work=Forbes India |date=19 December 2018 |accessdate=20 December 2018 }}</ref> He was also featured by ''[[GQ (magazine)|GQ]]'' in their listing of the 50 most influential young Indians of 2017 and 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/ranveer-singh-badshah-rajkummar-rao-at-gqs-50-most-influential-young-indians-of-2017-3790559.html|title=Ranveer Singh, Badshah, Rajkummar Rao at GQ's 50 Most Influential Young Indians of 2017|work=Firstpost|date=8 July 2017|accessdate=22 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180822163555/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/ranveer-singh-badshah-rajkummar-rao-at-gqs-50-most-influential-young-indians-of-2017-3790559.html|archive-date=22 August 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Sethi|first=Shikha|url=https://www.gqindia.com/influence-list/content/the-gq-50-most-influential-young-indians-of-2019|title=Here's the full list of GQ's 50 most influential young Indians of 2019|work=GQ|date=12 December 2019|accessdate=16 January 2020}}</ref> In 2019, ''[[India Today]]'' featured him among the nation's 50 most powerful people.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/the-most-powerful-people-of-india-2019-full-list-1574021-2019-07-26 |title=The most powerful people of India 2019 |work=India Today |date=26 July 2019 |accessdate=30 July 2019 }}</ref>\n\nIn addition to his acting career, Singh endorses several brands,<ref name=livemint>{{Cite news|url=http://www.livemint.com/Consumer/XDN4pSQNquOu3hwsMfdxOK/Why-brands-are-going-crazy-over-Ranveer-Singh.html |title=Why brands are going crazy over Ranveer Singh |last=Tewari |first=Saumya |date=14 October 2016 |newspaper