: 4\u00d7 Platinum<ref name=\"riaa\">{{cite web|title=Gold & Platinum: Fort Minor |url=http://riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?table=SEARCH_RESULTS&artist=Fort_Minor&format=&go=Search&perPage=50 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130201144059/http://riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?table=SEARCH_RESULTS&artist=Fort_Minor&format=&go=Search&perPage=50 |url-status=dead |archive-date=February 1, 2013 |publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of America]] |accessdate=December 30, 2011 }}</ref>\n* [[British Phonographic Industry|BPI]]: Silver<ref name=\"BPI\">{{cite web | url=https://www.bpi.co.uk/bpi-awards/ | title=Certified Awards Search | publisher=[[British Phonographic Industry]] | accessdate=April 28, 2017 | format=enter \"Fort Minor\" into the \"Search BPI Awards\" box}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Believe Me (Fort Minor song)|Believe Me]]\"<br/><small>(featuring [[Eric \"Bobo\" Correa|Eric Bobo]] & Styles of Beyond)</small>\n| \u2014 || 43 || 47 || 5 || \u2014 || 29 || 58 || \u2014 || \u2014 || 92\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Where'd You Go (Fort Minor song)|Where'd You Go]]\"<br/><small>(featuring [[Skylar Grey|Holly Brook]] & [[Jonah Matranga]])</small>\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2006\n| 4 || 41 || 29 || 8 || 24 || 18 || 15 || 14 || 62 || \u2014\n|\n* RIAA: Platinum<ref name=\"riaa\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[S.C.O.M. / Dolla / Get It / Spraypaint & Ink Pens]]\" <small>(Promo CD)</small><br/><small>(\"S.C.O.M.\" performed by Ryu featuring [[Juelz Santana]] & [[Celph Titled]] / \"Dolla\" performed by Fort Minor featuring Styles of Beyond / \"Get It\" performed by Styles of Beyond / \"Spraypaint & Inkpens\" performed by [[Ghostface Killah]] featuring Mike Shinoda and [[Lupe Fiasco]])</small>\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n| ''Fort Minor: We Major''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Welcome (Fort Minor song)|Welcome]]\"\n| 2015\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\n|{{n/a|Non-album single}}\n|-\n|colspan=\"14\" style=\"font-size:90%\"| \"\u2014\" denotes a recording that did not chart or was not released in that territory.\n|}\n\n===Fort Minor Militia exclusive tracks===\n[[Fort Minor Militia EP|''Militia'']] is the debut studio EP for the Fort Minor's official fan club, known as the \"Fort Minor Militia\". Subscribers were given exclusive tracks for digital download that were never officially released with the exception of \"Kenji (Interview Version)\" and \"Believe Me (Club Remix)\", which were later released to Linkin Park and Styles of Beyond's official websites respectively. These tracks are sometimes referred to as the ''Fort Minor Militia EP''.\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Date\n!Title\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|November 2005\n|\"Do What We Did\" <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(Demo) (featuring Styles of Beyond)</span>\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|December 2005\n|\"Kenji\" <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(Interview Version)</span>\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|January 2006\n|\"Tools of the Trade\" <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(Demo) (featuring Styles of Beyond & Celph Titled)</span>\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|February 2006\n|\"Where'd You Joe?\" <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(\"[[Where'd You Go (Fort Minor song)|Where'd You Go]]\" Remix by [[Joe Hahn|Mr. Hahn]]) (featuring Holly Brook)</span>\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|April 2006\n|\"Believe Me\" <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(Club Remix) (featuring Eric Bobo & Styles of Beyond)</span>\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|May 2006\n|\"Start It All Up\" <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(Demo)</span>\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|June 2006\n|\"Move On\" <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(Demo) (featuring Mr. Hahn)</span>\n|}\n\n===Music videos===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Date\n!Title\n!Director\n|-\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=\"1\"|January 12, 2005\n|\"Petrified\" \n|[[Robert Hales (director)|Robert Hales]]\n|-\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=\"1\"|February 26, 2005\n|\"Remember the Name\"\n|[[Kimo Proudfoot]]\n|-\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=\"1\"|December 12, 2005\n|\"Believe Me\"\n|Laurent Briet\n|-\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=\"1\"|May 29, 2006\n|\"Where'd You Go\"\n|[[Philip Andelman]]\n|-\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=\"1\"|June 22, 2015\n|\"Welcome\"\n|Jeff Nicholas\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n===[[MTV Video Music Awards]]===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:80%;\"\n|-\n! width=5%|Year\n! style=\"width:30%;\"| Award\n! style=\"width:30%;\"| Nomination\n! style=\"width:10%;\"| Result\n|-\n|[[2006 MTV Video Music Awards|2006]]\n|[[MTV Video Music Award for Ringtone of the Year|Ringtone of the Year]] \n|\"Where'd You Go\" (featuring [[Holly Brook]])\n|{{won}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.fortminor.com Fort Minor's Official Website]\n\n{{Fort Minor}}\n{{Mike Shinoda}}\n{{Linkin Park}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:American hip hop groups]]\n[[Category:Musical groups from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Linkin Park]]\n[[Category:Warner Records artists]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2004]]\n[[Category:Alternative hip hop groups]]\n[[Category:Rap rock groups]]\n", "name_user": "St. Jimmy Jammy", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fort_Minor"}
